  "text": "The Rust compiler's type inference architecture is organized across three key components:\n\n1. **InferCtxt** (compiler/rustc_infer/src/infer/mod.rs, line 231)\n   - The main inference context struct that drives the entire type inference engine\n   - Generic over 'tcx (the lifetime of the type context)\n   - Contains the TyCtxt (global type context), typing mode, and region constraint information\n   - Key fields: tcx (TyCtxt<'tcx>), typing_mode (TypingMode<'tcx>), considering_regions (bool)\n   - Manages inference variables, unification, and constraint solving\n\n2. **FnCtxt** (compiler/rustc_hir_typeck/src/fn_ctxt/mod.rs, line 44)\n   - The function-level type checker that handles type inference within individual functions\n   - Generic over 'a (lifetime of the inherited context) and 'tcx (type context lifetime)\n   - Wraps the InferCtxt and adds function-specific information like body_id, param_env, return type coercion\n   - Key fields: body_id (LocalDefId), param_env (ty::ParamEnv<'tcx>), ret_coercion (Option<RefCell<DynamicCoerceMany<'tcx>>>)\n   - Used to type-check function bodies and manage expectations for expressions\n\n3. **TypeVariableOrigin** (compiler/rustc_infer/src/infer/type_variable.rs, line 94)\n   - A struct tracking the metadata about how type variables are created and used\n   - Copy, Clone, and Debug traits implemented\n   - Key fields: span (Span), param_def_id (Option<DefId>)\n   - Provides diagnostic information about where type variables originated from\n   - Used internally by the type variable storage system to track variable provenance\n\nThese three components work together: InferCtxt provides the core inference engine, FnCtxt adds function-level context, and TypeVariableOrigin tracks metadata about type variables created during inference."
}

